<FeaturePage
  title="Optimistic Updates"
  description="UI updates land instantly. Sync happens in the background. No more spinners after a click."
  badge="Core · Library"
  activePath="/features"
>
  <p>
    sp00ky writes hit your local store the instant you call them — a mutation returns synchronously,
    your UI re-renders in the same frame, and the network round-trip runs in parallel. If the
    server disagrees, sp00ky reconciles and your UI corrects itself; if the network is unreachable,
    the write is durable on-device and replays when you reconnect.
  </p>
  <p>
    The result: apps that feel instantaneous even on spotty connections, with no hand-rolled
    optimistic state or queue logic in your components.
  </p>
  <h2>How it works</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Mutations write through a local SurrealDB replica before hitting the wire.</li>
    <li>Reactive queries re-emit immediately from the replica.</li>
    <li>A background worker reconciles with the server; conflicts use CRDT merge rules.</li>
    <li>Failures bubble as recoverable errors — never lost writes.</li>
  </ul>
</FeaturePage>
